news.headline: ADP National Employment Report: 122K Private Jobs Added In December
news.summary: The ADP employment report revealed that 122,000 nonfarm private jobs were added in December, lower than the expected 139,000 addition.

news.headline: December jobs report expected to show hiring slowdown, steady unemployment rate
news.summary: Economists expect the latest jobs report to show the labor market continued to cool in December but not enough to prompt a Federal Reserve interest rate cut in January.

news.headline: Carter Funeral Suspends Stock Market; What to Expect Friday
news.summary: Expectations are for 155K jobs to have been filled in December, with an Unemployment Rate holding steady at +4.2%.

news.headline: SPY: 2025 Promises To Be More Challenging
news.summary: The S&P 500 ETF saw a +24.9% gain in 2024, driven primarily by AI and tech, but rising yields pose risks now.

news.headline: Shrinking Trade Between The U.S., China, And The Rest Of The World
news.summary: The total value of goods traded between the United States, China, and the rest of the world remained depressed in November 2024.
